205 int32_t MmwDemo_gen_twiddle_fft32x32_fast(int32_t *w, int32_t n, double scale)
206  {
207  int32_t i, j, k;
208  int32_t log2n = 30 - _norm(n); //Note n is always power of 2
209  int32_t step = 1024 >> log2n;
210  int32_t step6 = 3 * step;
211  int32_t step4 = 2 * step;
212  int32_t step2 = 1 * step;
213  int32_t ind, indLsb, indMsb;
214  int64_t * restrict table = (int64_t *) twiddleTableCommon;
215  int64_t * restrict wd = (int64_t *) w;
216  int32_t xRe;
217  int32_t xIm;
218 
219  for (j = 1, k = 0; j < n >> 2; j = j << 2) {
220  for (i =0; i < n >> 2; i += j) {
221  ind = step2 * (i);
222  indLsb = ind & 0xFF;
223  indMsb = (ind >> 8) & 0x3;
224  xRe = _hill(table[indLsb]);
225  xIm = _loll(table[indLsb]);
226  if (indMsb == 0)
227  {
228  wd[k + 0] = _itoll(xRe, xIm);
229  }
230  if (indMsb == 1)
231  {
232  wd[k + 0] = _itoll(-xIm, xRe);
233  }
234  if (indMsb == 2)
235  {
236  wd[k + 0] = _itoll(-xRe, -xIm);
237  }
238 
239  ind = step4 * (i);
240  indLsb = ind & 0xFF;
241  indMsb = (ind >> 8) & 0x3;
242  xRe = _hill(table[indLsb]);
243  xIm = _loll(table[indLsb]);
244  if (indMsb == 0)
245  {
246  wd[k + 1] = _itoll(xRe, xIm);
247  }
248  if (indMsb == 1)
249  {
250  wd[k + 1] = _itoll(-xIm, xRe);
251  }
252  if (indMsb == 2)
253  {
254  wd[k + 1] = _itoll(-xRe, -xIm);
255  }
256 
257  ind = step6 * (i);
258  indLsb = ind & 0xFF;
259  indMsb = (ind >> 8) & 0x3;
260  xRe = _hill(table[indLsb]);
261  xIm = _loll(table[indLsb]);
262  if (indMsb == 0)
263  {
264  wd[k + 2] = _itoll(xRe, xIm);
265  }
266  if (indMsb == 1)
267  {
268  wd[k + 2] = _itoll(-xIm, xRe);
269  }

271  {
272  wd[k + 2] = _itoll(-xRe, -xIm);
273  }
274

277  }

542 int32_t MmwDemo_getDopplerLine(MmwDemo_1D_DopplerLines_t * ths)
543 {
544  uint32_t index = ths->currentIndex;
545  uint32_t word = index >> 5;
546  uint32_t bit = index & 31;
547 
548  while (((ths->dopplerLineMask[word] >> bit) & 0x1) == 0)
549  {
550  index++;
551  bit++;
552  if (bit == 32)
553  {
554  word++;
555  bit = 0;
556  if (word >= ths->dopplerLineMaskLen)
557  {
558  MmwDemo_dssAssert(0);
559  }
560  }
561  }
562  ths->currentIndex = index + 1;
563  return index;
564 }

603 void MmwDemo_XYcalc (MmwDemo_DSS_DataPathObj *obj,
604  uint32_t objIndex,
605  uint16_t azimIdx,
606  float maxVal)
607 {
608  int32_t sMaxIdx;
609  float temp;
610  float Wx;
611  float range;
612  float x, y;
613  uint32_t xyzOutputQFormat = obj->xyzOutputQFormat;
614 #define ONE_QFORMAT (1 << xyzOutputQFormat)
615  float rangeResolution = obj->rangeResolution;
616 
617 
618  uint32_t numAngleBins = obj->numAngleBins;
619  uint32_t numDopplerBins = obj->numDopplerBins;
620  uint32_t numRangeBins = obj->numRangeBins;
621 
622 
623  obj->detObj2dAzimIdx[objIndex] = azimIdx;
624 
625  /* Save square root of maximum peak to object peak value scaling */
626  temp = divsp(maxVal, (numRangeBins * numAngleBins * numDopplerBins));
627  obj->detObj2D[objIndex].peakVal = (uint16_t)sqrtsp(temp);
628 
629  /* Calculate X and Y coordinates in meters in Q format */
630 #ifdef MMW_ENABLE_NEGATIVE_FREQ_SLOPE
631  if (rangeResolution > 0)
632  {
633  range = obj->detObj2D[objIndex].rangeIdx * rangeResolution;
634  }
635  else
636  {
637  obj->detObj2D[objIndex].rangeIdx = (uint16_t) ((int32_t) obj->numRangeBins - (int32_t) obj->detObj2D[objIndex].rangeIdx);
638  range = obj->detObj2D[objIndex].rangeIdx * -rangeResolution;
639  }
640 #else
641  range = obj->detObj2D[objIndex].rangeIdx * rangeResolution;
642 #endif
643 
644  /* Compensate for range bias */
645  range -= obj->cliCommonCfg->compRxChanCfg.rangeBias;
646  if (range < 0)
647  {
648  range = 0;
649  }
650 
651  if(azimIdx > (numAngleBins/2 -1))
652  {
653  sMaxIdx = azimIdx - numAngleBins;
654  }
655  else
656  {
657  sMaxIdx = azimIdx;
658  }
659 
660  Wx = 2 * (float) sMaxIdx / numAngleBins;
661  x = range * Wx;
662 
663  /* y = sqrt(range^2 - x^2) */
664  temp = range*range -x*x ;
665  if (temp > 0)
666  {
667  y = sqrtsp(temp);
668  }
669  else
670  {
671  y = 0;
672  }
673 
674  /* Convert to Q format */
675  obj->detObj2D[objIndex].x = (int16_t) ROUND(x * ONE_QFORMAT);
676  obj->detObj2D[objIndex].y = (int16_t) ROUND(y * ONE_QFORMAT);
677  obj->detObj2D[objIndex].z = 0;
678 }

697 void MmwDemo_XYestimation(MmwDemo_DSS_DataPathObj *obj,
698  uint32_t objIndex)
699 {
700  uint32_t i;
701  float *azimuthMagSqr = obj->azimuthMagSqr;
702  uint32_t numAngleBins = obj->numAngleBins;
703  uint32_t numSearchBins;
704 
705  uint32_t azimIdx = 0;
706  float maxVal = 0;
707 
708  if(obj->cliCfg->extendedMaxVelocityCfg.enabled && (obj->numVirtualAntAzim > obj->numRxAntennas))
709  {
710  numSearchBins = numAngleBins * 2;
711  }
712  else
713  {
714  numSearchBins = numAngleBins;
715  }
716  /* Find peak position - search in original and flipped output */
717  for (i = 0; i < numSearchBins ; i++)
718  {
719  if (azimuthMagSqr[i] > maxVal)
720  {
721  azimIdx = i;
722  maxVal = azimuthMagSqr[i];
723  }
724  }
725  if(obj->cliCfg->extendedMaxVelocityCfg.enabled && (obj->numVirtualAntAzim > obj->numRxAntennas))
726  {
727  if(azimIdx >= numAngleBins)
728  {
729  /* Velocity aliased: |velocity| > Vmax */
730  /* Correct peak index: */
731  azimIdx -= numAngleBins;
732  /* Correct velocity */
733  if (obj->detObj2D[objIndex].dopplerIdx < 0)
734  {
735  obj->detObj2D[objIndex].dopplerIdx += (int16_t) obj->numDopplerBins;
736  }
737  else
738  {
739  obj->detObj2D[objIndex].dopplerIdx -= (int16_t) obj->numDopplerBins;
740  }
741  }
742  }
743 
744  MmwDemo_XYcalc (obj,
745  objIndex,
746  azimIdx,
747  maxVal);
748 
749  /* Check for second peak */
750  if (obj->cliCfg->multiObjBeamFormingCfg.enabled && (!obj->cliCfg->extendedMaxVelocityCfg.enabled))
751  {
752  uint32_t leftSearchIdx;
753  uint32_t rightSearchIdx;
754  uint32_t secondSearchLen;
755  uint32_t iModAzimLen;
756  float maxVal2;
757  int32_t k;
758 
759  /* Find right edge of the first peak */
760  i = azimIdx;
761  leftSearchIdx = (i + 1) & (numAngleBins-1);
762  k = numAngleBins;
763  while ((azimuthMagSqr[i] >= azimuthMagSqr[leftSearchIdx]) && (k > 0))
764  {
765  i = (i + 1) & (numAngleBins-1);
766  leftSearchIdx = (leftSearchIdx + 1) & (numAngleBins-1);
767  k--;
768  }
769 
770  /* Find left edge of the first peak */
771  i = azimIdx;
772  rightSearchIdx = (i - 1) & (numAngleBins-1);
773  k = numAngleBins;
774  while ((azimuthMagSqr[i] >= azimuthMagSqr[rightSearchIdx]) && (k > 0))
775  {
776  i = (i - 1) & (numAngleBins-1);
777  rightSearchIdx = (rightSearchIdx - 1) & (numAngleBins-1);
778  k--;
779  }
780 
781  secondSearchLen = ((rightSearchIdx - leftSearchIdx) & (numAngleBins-1)) + 1;
782  /* Find second peak */
783  maxVal2 = azimuthMagSqr[leftSearchIdx];
784  azimIdx = leftSearchIdx;
785  for (i = leftSearchIdx; i < (leftSearchIdx + secondSearchLen); i++)
786  {
787  iModAzimLen = i & (numAngleBins-1);
788  if (azimuthMagSqr[iModAzimLen] > maxVal2)
789  {
790  azimIdx = iModAzimLen;
791  maxVal2 = azimuthMagSqr[iModAzimLen];
792  }
793  }
794 
795  /* Is second peak greater than threshold? */
796  if (maxVal2 > (maxVal * obj->cliCfg->multiObjBeamFormingCfg.multiPeakThrsScal) && (obj->numDetObj < MMW_MAX_OBJ_OUT))
797  {
798  /* Second peak detected! Add it to the end of the list */
799  obj->detObj2D[obj->numDetObj].dopplerIdx = obj->detObj2D[objIndex].dopplerIdx;
800  obj->detObj2D[obj->numDetObj].rangeIdx = obj->detObj2D[objIndex].rangeIdx;
801  objIndex = obj->numDetObj;
802  obj->numDetObj++;
803 
804  MmwDemo_XYcalc (obj,
805  objIndex,
806  azimIdx,
807  maxVal2);
808  }
809  }
810 }

1201 void MmwDemo_EDMA_CQTransferCompletionCallbackFxn(uintptr_t arg,
1202  uint8_t transferCompletionCode)
1203 {
1204  MmwDemo_DSS_DataPathObj *obj = (MmwDemo_DSS_DataPathObj *)arg;
1205  uint8_t chirpIdx;
1206 
1207  switch (transferCompletionCode)
1208  {
1209  /* Validate numSlices from data buffer for every chirp.
1210  Note1: If the configured number of slices covers more time period than the sampling time,
1211  the actual reported number of slices maybe smaller.
1212 
1213  Note 2: If there are extensive CQ data processing,
1214  then the processing code should be moved to a task
1215  */
1216 
1217  case MMW_EDMA_CH_SIGIMG_MON:
1218  obj->datapathCQ.sigImgEdmaCnt++;
1219  for(chirpIdx = 0; chirpIdx < obj->numChirpsPerChirpEvent; chirpIdx++)
1220  {
1221  uint8_t *sigImgData = obj->datapathCQ.sigImgData;
1222 
1223  if(sigImgData[chirpIdx * obj->datapathCQ.sigImgMonDataSizePerChirp] > obj->datapathCQ.sigImgMonCfg->numSlices)
1224  {
1225  obj->datapathCQ.sigImgErrCnt++;
1226  MmwDemo_dssAssert(0);
1227  }
1228  }
1229  break;
1230 
1231  case MMW_EDMA_CH_RX_SATURATION_MON:
1232  obj->datapathCQ.rxSatEdmaCnt++;
1233  for(chirpIdx = 0; chirpIdx < obj->numChirpsPerChirpEvent; chirpIdx++)
1234  {
1235  uint8_t *rxSatData = obj->datapathCQ.rxSatData;
1236  if(rxSatData[chirpIdx * obj->datapathCQ.satMonDataSizePerChirp] > obj->datapathCQ.rxSatMonCfg->numSlices)
1237  {
1238  obj->datapathCQ.rxSatErrCnt++;
1239  MmwDemo_dssAssert(0);
1240  }
1241  }
1242  break;
1243 
1244  default:

1707 uint32_t MmwDemo_cfarPeakGrouping(
1708  MmwDemo_detectedObj* objOut,
1709  MmwDemo_objRaw_t * objRaw,
1710  uint32_t numDetectedObjects,
1711  uint16_t* detMatrix,
1712  uint32_t numDopplerBins,
1713  uint32_t maxRangeIdx,
1714  uint32_t minRangeIdx,
1715  uint32_t groupInDopplerDirection,
1716  uint32_t groupInRangeDirection)
1717 {
1718  int32_t i, j;
1719  int32_t rowStart, rowEnd;
1720  uint32_t numObjOut = 0;
1721  uint32_t rangeIdx, dopplerIdx, peakVal;
1722  uint16_t *tempPtr;
1723  uint16_t kernel[9], detectedObjFlag;
1724  int32_t k, l;
1725  uint32_t startInd, stepInd, endInd;
1726 
1727  if ((groupInDopplerDirection == 1) && (groupInRangeDirection == 1))
1728  {
1729  /* Grouping both in Range and Doppler direction */
1730  startInd = 0;
1731  stepInd = 1;
1732  endInd = 8;
1733  }
1734  else if ((groupInDopplerDirection == 0) && (groupInRangeDirection == 1))
1735  {
1736  /* Grouping only in Range direction */
1737  startInd = 1;
1738  stepInd = 3;
1739  endInd = 7;
1740  }
1741  else if ((groupInDopplerDirection == 1) && (groupInRangeDirection == 0))
1742  {
1743  /* Grouping only in Doppler direction */
1744  startInd = 3;
1745  stepInd = 1;
1746  endInd = 5;
1747  }
1748  else
1749  {
1750  /* No grouping, copy all detected objects to the output matrix within specified min max range*/
1751  for(i = 0; i < MIN(numDetectedObjects, MMW_MAX_OBJ_OUT) ; i++)
1752  {
1753  if ((objRaw[i].rangeIdx <= maxRangeIdx) && ((objRaw[i].rangeIdx >= minRangeIdx)))
1754  {
1755  objOut[numObjOut].rangeIdx = objRaw[i].rangeIdx;
1756  objOut[numObjOut].dopplerIdx = DOPPLER_IDX_TO_SIGNED(objRaw[i].dopplerIdx, numDopplerBins);
1757  objOut[numObjOut].peakVal = objRaw[i].peakVal;
1758  numObjOut++;
1759  }
1760  }
1761  return numObjOut;
1762  }
1763 
1764  /* Start checking */
1765  for(i = 0; i < numDetectedObjects; i++)
1766  {
1767  detectedObjFlag = 0;
1768  rangeIdx = objRaw[i].rangeIdx;
1769  dopplerIdx = objRaw[i].dopplerIdx;
1770  peakVal = objRaw[i].peakVal;
1771  if((rangeIdx <= maxRangeIdx) && (rangeIdx >= minRangeIdx))
1772  {
1773  detectedObjFlag = 1;
1774 
1775  /* Fill local 3x3 kernel from detection matrix in L3*/
1776  tempPtr = detMatrix + (rangeIdx-1)*numDopplerBins;
1777  rowStart = 0;
1778  rowEnd = 2;
1779  if (rangeIdx == minRangeIdx)
1780  {
1781  tempPtr = detMatrix + (rangeIdx)*numDopplerBins;
1782  rowStart = 1;
1783  memset((void *) kernel, 0, 3 * sizeof(uint16_t));
1784  }
1785  else if (rangeIdx == maxRangeIdx)
1786  {
1787  rowEnd = 1;
1788  memset((void *) &kernel[6], 0, 3 * sizeof(uint16_t));
1789  }
1790 
1791  for (j = rowStart; j <= rowEnd; j++)
1792  {
1793  for (k = 0; k < 3; k++)
1794  {
1795  l = dopplerIdx + (k - 1);
1796  if(l < 0)
1797  {
1798  l += numDopplerBins;
1799  }
1800  else if(l >= numDopplerBins)
1801  {
1802  l -= numDopplerBins;
1803  }
1804  kernel[j*3+k] = tempPtr[l];
1805  }
1806  tempPtr += numDopplerBins;
1807  }
1808  /* Compare the detected object to its neighbors.
1809  * Detected object is at index 4*/
1810  for (k = startInd; k <= endInd; k += stepInd)
1811  {
1812  if(kernel[k] > kernel[4])
1813  {
1814  detectedObjFlag = 0;
1815  }
1816  }
1817  }
1818  if (detectedObjFlag == 1)
1819  {
1820  objOut[numObjOut].rangeIdx = rangeIdx;
1821  objOut[numObjOut].dopplerIdx = DOPPLER_IDX_TO_SIGNED(dopplerIdx, numDopplerBins);
1822  objOut[numObjOut].peakVal = peakVal;
1823  numObjOut++;
1824  }
1825  if (numObjOut >= MMW_MAX_OBJ_OUT)
1826  {
1827  break;
1828  }
1829 
1830  }
1831 
1832  return(numObjOut);
1833 }

1923  {

1926  dopplerIdx = objRaw[i].dopplerIdx;
1927  peakVal = objRaw[i].peakVal;
1928 
1929  if((rangeIdx <= maxRangeIdx) && (rangeIdx >= minRangeIdx))
1930  {
1931  detectedObjFlag = 1;
1932  memset((void *) kernel, 0, 9*sizeof(uint16_t));
1933 
1934  /* Fill the middle column of the kernel */
1935  kernel[4] = peakVal;
1936 
1937  if (i > 0)
1938  {
1939  if ((objRaw[i-1].rangeIdx == (rangeIdx-1)) &&
1940  (objRaw[i-1].dopplerIdx == dopplerIdx))
1941  {
1942  kernel[1] = objRaw[i-1].peakVal;

1944  }

1975  {

1978  k = WRAP_UP_LIST_IDX(k-1);
1979  }

1982  k = WRAP_DWN_LIST_IDX(i+1);

1984  {

1999  else if ((objRaw[k].rangeIdx == (rangeIdx + 1)) &&
2000  (objRaw[k].dopplerIdx == WRAP_DOPPLER_IDX(dopplerIdx + 1)))
2001  {

2003  }
2004  k = WRAP_DWN_LIST_IDX(k+1);
2005  }

2008  * Detected object is at index 4*/

2010  {
2011  if(kernel[k] > kernel[4])
2012  {

2014  }
2015  }

2021  objOut[numObjOut].peakVal = peakVal;
2022  numObjOut++;
2023  }
2024  if (numObjOut >= MMW_MAX_OBJ_OUT)
2025  {
2026  break;
2027  }
2028  }
2029

2246 /*!*****************************************************************************************************************
2247  * \brief
2248  * Function Name : MmwDemo_DopplerCompensation
2249  *
2250  * \par
2251  * <b>Description</b> : Compensation of Doppler phase shift in the virtual antennas,
2252  * (corresponding to second Tx antenna chirps). Symbols
2253  * corresponding to virtual antennas, are rotated by half
2254  * of the Doppler phase shift measured by Doppler FFT.
2255  * The phase shift read from the table using half of the
2256  * object Doppler index value. If the Doppler index is
2257  * odd, an extra half of the bin phase shift is added.
2258  *
2259  * @param[in] dopplerIdx : Doppler index of the object
2260  *
2261  * @param[in] numDopplerBins : Number of Doppler bins
2262  *
2263  * @param[in] azimuthModCoefs: Table with cos/sin values SIN in even position, COS in odd position
2264  * exp(1j*2*pi*k/N) for k=0,...,N-1 where N is number of Doppler bins.
2265  *
2266  * @param[out] azimuthModCoefsHalfBin : exp(1j*2*pi* 0.5 /N)
2267  *
2268  * @param[in,out] azimuthIn :Pointer to antenna symbols to be Doppler compensated
2269  *
2270  * @param[in] numAnt : Number of antenna symbols to be Doppler compensated
2271  *
2272  * @return void
2273  *
2274  *******************************************************************************************************************
2275  */
2276 void MmwDemo_addDopplerCompensation(int32_t dopplerIdx,
2277  int32_t numDopplerBins,
2278  uint32_t *azimuthModCoefs,
2279  uint32_t *azimuthModCoefsHalfBin,
2280  int64_t *azimuthIn,
2281  uint32_t numAnt)
2282 {
2283  uint32_t expDoppComp;
2284  int32_t dopplerCompensationIdx = dopplerIdx;
2285  int64_t azimuthVal;
2286  int32_t Re, Im;
2287  uint32_t antIndx;
2288 
2289  if (numAnt == 0)
2290  {
2291  return;
2292  }
2293 
2294  /*Divide Doppler index by 2*/
2295  if (dopplerCompensationIdx >= numDopplerBins/2)
2296  {
2297  dopplerCompensationIdx -= (int32_t)numDopplerBins;
2298  }
2299  dopplerCompensationIdx = dopplerCompensationIdx / 2;
2300  if (dopplerCompensationIdx < 0)
2301  {
2302  dopplerCompensationIdx += (int32_t) numDopplerBins;
2303  }
2304  expDoppComp = azimuthModCoefs[dopplerCompensationIdx];
2305  /* Add half bin rotation if Doppler index was odd */
2306  if (dopplerIdx & 0x1)
2307  {
2308  expDoppComp = _cmpyr1(expDoppComp, *azimuthModCoefsHalfBin);
2309  }

2313  {
2314  azimuthVal = _amem8(&azimuthIn[antIndx]);

2316  _mpylir(expDoppComp, _hill(azimuthVal)));
2317  Im = _sadd(_mpylir(expDoppComp, _loll(azimuthVal)),
2318  _mpyhir(expDoppComp, _hill(azimuthVal)));

2485 #define MMWDEMO_TWO_PI_OVER_LAMBDA (2. * PI_ / MMWDEMO_XWR16XX_EVM_77GHZ_LAMBDA)
2486 
2487  int32_t i;
2488  float range;
2489  float rangeSq;
2490  cmplx32ReIm_t * azimuthOut0 = obj->azimuthOut;
2491  cmplx32ReIm_t * azimuthOut1 = &obj->azimuthOut[obj->numAngleBins];

2493  float corrReal;
2494  float corrImag;

2496  float theta;
2497  float thetaInc = 2.0 / (float) obj->numAngleBins;

2499  float psi;

2501  range = (obj->detObj2D[detIdx2].rangeIdx * obj->rangeResolution -
2502  obj->cliCommonCfg->compRxChanCfg.rangeBias) * 1000;
2503  rangeSq = range * range;
2504 
2505  corrReal = 1.0;
2506  corrImag = 0.0;
2507 
2508  for (i = 0; i < numAngleBins; i++)
2509  {

2511  {

2513  }
2514  else
2515  {

2519  rx4 = sqrtsp(rangeSq + MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_DB_SQ - range * theta * MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_DB2);
2520  tx2 = sqrtsp(rangeSq + MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_AB_SQ - range * theta * MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_AB2);
2521  rx1 = sqrtsp(rangeSq + MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_EB_SQ - range * theta * MMWDEMO_NEAR_FIELD_EB2);
2522 
2523  if (range > 0)

2526  corrReal = cossp(psi);
2527  corrImag = sinsp(-psi);
2528  }

2530  azimuthOut1Corr.real = (int32_t) (azimuthOut1[i].real * corrReal - azimuthOut1[i].imag * corrImag);

2533  azimuthOut0[i].imag = azimuthOut0[i].imag + azimuthOut1Corr.imag;
2534  }

3844 void MmwDemo_genWindow(void *win,
3845  uint32_t windowDatumType,
3846  uint32_t winLen,
3847  uint32_t winGenLen,
3848  int32_t oneQformat,
3849  uint32_t winType)
3850 {
3851  uint32_t winIndx;
3852  int32_t winVal;
3853  int16_t * win16 = (int16_t *) win;
3854  int32_t * win32 = (int32_t *) win;
3855 
3856  float eR = 1.;
3857  float eI = 0.;
3858  float e2R = 1.;
3859  float e2I = 0.;
3860  float ephyR, ephyI;
3861  float e2phyR, e2phyI;
3862  float tmpR;
3863 
3864  float phi = 2 * PI_ / ((float) winLen - 1);
3865 
3866 
3867  ephyR = cossp(phi);
3868  ephyI = sinsp(phi);
3869 
3870  e2phyR = ephyR * ephyR - ephyI * ephyI;
3871  e2phyI = 2 * ephyR * ephyI;
3872 
3873 
3874  if(winType == MMW_WIN_BLACKMAN)
3875  {
3876  //Blackman window
3877  float a0 = 0.42;
3878  float a1 = 0.5;
3879  float a2 = 0.08;
3880  for(winIndx = 0; winIndx < winGenLen; winIndx++)
3881  {
3882  winVal = (int32_t) ((oneQformat * (a0 - a1*eR + a2*e2R)) + 0.5);
3883  if(winVal >= oneQformat)
3884  {
3885  winVal = oneQformat - 1;
3886  }
3887  if (windowDatumType == FFT_WINDOW_INT16)
3888  {
3889  win16[winIndx] = (int16_t) winVal;
3890  }
3891  if (windowDatumType == FFT_WINDOW_INT32)
3892  {
3893  win32[winIndx] = (int32_t) winVal;
3894  }
3895  tmpR = eR;
3896  eR = eR * ephyR - eI * ephyI;
3897  eI = tmpR * ephyI + eI * ephyR;
3898 
3899  tmpR = e2R;
3900  e2R = e2R * e2phyR - e2I * e2phyI;
3901  e2I = tmpR * e2phyI + e2I * e2phyR;
3902  }
3903  }
3904  else if (winType == MMW_WIN_HANNING)
3905  {
3906  //Hanning window
3907  for(winIndx = 0; winIndx < winGenLen; winIndx++)
3908  {
3909  winVal = (int32_t) ((oneQformat * 0.5* (1 - eR)) + 0.5);
3910  if(winVal >= oneQformat)
3911  {
3912  winVal = oneQformat - 1;
3913  }
3914  if (windowDatumType == FFT_WINDOW_INT16)
3915  {
3916  win16[winIndx] = (int16_t) winVal;
3917  }
3918  if (windowDatumType == FFT_WINDOW_INT32)
3919  {
3920  win32[winIndx] = (int32_t) winVal;
3921  }
3922  tmpR = eR;
3923  eR = eR*ephyR - eI*ephyI;
3924  eI = tmpR*ephyI + eI*ephyR;
3925  }
3926  }
3927  else if (winType == MMW_WIN_RECT)
3928  {
3929  //Rectangular window
3930  for(winIndx = 0; winIndx < winGenLen; winIndx++)
3931  {
3932  if (windowDatumType == FFT_WINDOW_INT16)
3933  {
3934  win16[winIndx] = (int16_t) (oneQformat-1);
3935  }
3936  if (windowDatumType == FFT_WINDOW_INT32)
3937  {
3938  win32[winIndx] = (int32_t) (oneQformat-1);
3939  }
3940  }
3941  }
3942 }
